*** INSTALLATION AND CONFIGURATION OF SQLMesh
 - using VSCODE  run the following command
 
 
 First, create the virtual environment:
	python -m venv .env
Then activate it:
	source .env/bin/activate
For windows 
 .env\Scripts\Activate.ps1
 
 
 Install the core SQLMesh library with pip
	pip install sqlmesh

Set up a local DuckDB instance:
- this will create config-yaml file for further configuration.

	sqlmesh init duckdb

Configure the ymal file to point to SQL database server

Configuration (config.yaml)
Hereâ€™s an example configuration file for MSSQL:

-------------------With MS SQL authentication---------------------------------------
gateways:
  mssql_gateway:
    connection:
      type: mssql
      host: your-mssql-server
      user: your-username
      password: your-password
      database: your-database
      port: 1433
      autocommit: true

default_gateway: mssql_gateway

model_defaults:
  dialect: tsql


====================


-----------------With Trusted Authentication
gateways:
  mssql_gateway:
    connection:
      type: mssql
      host: your-mssql-server
      database: your-database
      port: 1433
      trusted_connection: true

default_gateway: mssql_gateway

model_defaults:
  dialect: tsql

========================================


-----  OR ------

gateways:
  mssql_gateway:
    connection:
      type: mssql
      host: your-mssql-server
      database: your-database
      port: 1433
      driver: ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server
      authentication: Windows

default_gateway: mssql_gateway

model_defaults:
  dialect: mssql


